{
  "stem": "25591.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Some of us-- and I put myself into this category, and I don't know whether this is 1%, 10%, I don't think it's much higher than that-- have been made enormously resilient by-- by this experience, which speaking for myself, I still don't fully understand, although I read 100 books about it.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I cannot make sense of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But what I do is-- and this is, of course, why, thanks to my wife, much of my work has focused on human rights.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I mean, I am-- I shouldn't say I am.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My wife and because of my wife, my office has become the voice of human rights in the Congress of the United States-- human rights for Tibetans and-- and persecuted people all over.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I view this as a moral obligation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I realize that I'm making a very marginal difference, a very tiny difference, but I can't live my-- with myself if I don't make the maximum difference I've been privileged to be able to do as a member of Congress.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So I am very grateful that I survived, much less in a personal sense, but because I am sort of part of the forces of good in this world.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You know, many Holocaust survivors-- I mean a person like Elie Wiesel is the chronicler of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He's the conscience of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I've enormous admiration for Elie and for what-- what he has done, his enormous talents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Some have been financially successful and have been philanthropists for good causes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I've great respect for them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I have no money.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My-- my-- my work is in the Congress.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And through my work in the Congress, it really focuses on human rights.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
